00:39:42.412 --> 00:39:44.620
It means that there is excess
energy in this nucleus.

00:39:44.620 --> 00:39:46.930
So the difference between
ground state or whatever

00:39:46.930 --> 00:39:50.560
of iridium-192 and the
ground state of platinum-192

00:39:50.560 --> 00:39:53.500
is 1.4597 MeV.

00:39:53.500 --> 00:39:54.850
Notice I'm not rounding.

00:39:54.850 --> 00:39:56.380
Don't round.

00:39:56.380 --> 00:39:59.110
And we can end up with a beta
particle that doesn't quite

00:39:59.110 --> 00:40:01.780
release all that energy, leaving
some in the nucleus in what's

00:40:01.780 --> 00:40:03.190
called an excited state.

00:40:03.190 --> 00:40:05.500
It's analogous to
if you have, let's

00:40:05.500 --> 00:40:09.708
say, an atom of a, whatever
that happens to be.

00:40:09.708 --> 00:40:12.250
And since you started talking
