00:40:16.210 --> 00:40:18.640
And it only has two electrons.

00:40:18.640 --> 00:40:24.230
And one of them gained some
energy becoming excited up

00:40:24.230 --> 00:40:25.760
to the next energy level.

00:40:25.760 --> 00:40:28.730
Same thing, but on
the nuclear level,

00:40:28.730 --> 00:40:30.980
these excitations are
not in the eV range,

00:40:30.980 --> 00:40:32.570
they're in the MeV range.

00:40:32.570 --> 00:40:35.210
But you can think of it as a
precisely analogous process

00:40:35.210 --> 00:40:36.290
for the time being.

00:40:36.290 --> 00:40:38.660
There are excited
nuclear energy levels,

00:40:38.660 --> 00:40:41.600
and they can also decay
by photon emission--

00:40:41.600 --> 00:40:46.680
in this case, gamma emission
because the masses are

00:40:46.680 --> 00:40:47.850
basically the same.

00:40:47.850 --> 00:40:49.350
Remember that the
rest mass energies

00:40:49.350 --> 00:40:52.110
might be slightly different,
but the charge is the same.

00:40:52.110 --> 00:40:53.790
There's no real
change in momentum

00:40:53.790 --> 00:40:56.280
because this is a nucleus
that started at rest.

00:40:56.280 --> 00:40:59.480
And this way the energy
can be conserved.

00:40:59.480 --> 00:41:00.693
Yeah, Sean?

