00:46:32.840 --> 00:46:35.290
to get off this earth for a
significant amount of time,

00:46:35.290 --> 00:46:37.040
we have to deal with
the fact that there's

00:46:37.040 --> 00:46:39.740
no atmosphere in
space to shield us

00:46:39.740 --> 00:46:42.530
from the high-energy protons
and other cosmic rays that would

00:46:42.530 --> 00:46:45.380
otherwise, well, destroy life.

00:46:45.380 --> 00:46:47.690
So there's a lot of
interesting ideas,

00:46:47.690 --> 00:46:50.000
and a lot of problems
with astronaut shielding.

00:46:50.000 --> 00:46:52.640
One of them is that the
protons are so heavy--

00:46:52.640 --> 00:46:56.210
I'm sorry-- the protons are
so energetic that they're

00:46:56.210 --> 00:47:01.680
difficult to shield just
by mass attenuation.

00:47:01.680 --> 00:47:04.480
And the trick here is,
well, different radiation

00:47:04.480 --> 00:47:06.688
has different penetrating power.

00:47:06.688 --> 00:47:08.230
It depends on its
energy, but it also

00:47:08.230 --> 00:47:10.420
depends a lot on its charge.

00:47:10.420 --> 00:47:14.170
For example, alpha particles can
be stopped by a sheet of paper.

00:47:14.170 --> 00:47:17.357
These are the MeV
level helium nuclei.

00:47:17.357 --> 00:47:19.690
Like, if you hold an alpha
particle source in your hand,

00:47:19.690 --> 00:47:23.170
the dead skin on your hand stops
the alphas from getting in.

00:47:23.170 --> 00:47:25.930
Remember that, because I'm going
to be asking you a question

00:47:25.930 --> 00:47:28.510
later on to see who your
friends are and who they aren't.

00:47:28.510 --> 00:47:30.800
I don't know if anyone knows
what I'm talking about.

00:47:30.800 --> 00:47:32.980
But if you do,
don't give it away.

00:47:32.980 --> 00:47:37.210
Beta particles or electrons have
low mass and half the charge

00:47:37.210 --> 00:47:38.470
of an alpha particle.

00:47:38.470 --> 00:47:40.360
They can be able to
get through paper, even

00:47:40.360 --> 00:47:41.990
through a little bit of plastic.

00:47:41.990 --> 00:47:44.080
But a small bit of
metal can stop them.

00:47:44.080 --> 00:47:46.060
Gamma rays go right through.

00:47:46.060 --> 00:47:48.070
And notice that they've
been drawn not quite

00:47:48.070 --> 00:47:49.810
being stopped by
the concrete, which

00:47:49.810 --> 00:47:51.550
is a great shielding material.

00:47:51.550 --> 00:47:54.010
Because like I said before,
you can exponentially

00:47:54.010 --> 00:47:55.720
attenuate gamma rays.

00:47:55.720 --> 00:48:00.240
You can't with all certainty
stop every single one.

00:48:00.240 --> 00:48:02.790
So then how do you stop these
high-energy charged particles

00:48:02.790 --> 00:48:06.270
if the more energetic they
are, the more range they are?

00:48:06.270 --> 00:48:08.980
Boost your
electromagnetic field.

00:48:08.980 --> 00:48:11.790
So it's actually been
proposed to have spaceships

00:48:11.790 --> 00:48:15.360
with enormous magnetic fields
or electromagnetic fields

00:48:15.360 --> 00:48:17.610
around them to deflect
the protons away

00:48:17.610 --> 00:48:19.110
or around the ship.

00:48:19.110 --> 00:48:21.750
Because if you can't stop it
by putting matter in the way,

00:48:21.750 --> 00:48:23.292
rely on the fact
that they're charged

00:48:23.292 --> 00:48:26.540
particles, and will
curve around whatever

00:48:26.540 --> 00:48:28.860
has got a high electric
field around it.

00:48:28.860 --> 00:48:30.240
So this is one
way of, let's say,

00:48:30.240 --> 00:48:31.860
shielding deep space missions.

00:48:31.860 --> 00:48:34.640
If you can't put more stuff in
there because stuff is heavy,

00:48:34.640 --> 00:48:37.440
and launching stuff
into space is expensive,

00:48:37.440 --> 00:48:39.820
rely on electromagnetism.

00:48:39.820 --> 00:48:43.210
And there are also RTGs, or
Radio Thermal Generators,

00:48:43.210 --> 00:48:46.460
or Radio Isotope
Thermoelectric Generators,

00:48:46.460 --> 00:48:49.780
which are little balls of things
like plutonium or strontium

00:48:49.780 --> 00:48:51.830
that give off so
many alpha particles.

00:48:51.830 --> 00:48:54.100
And the alpha particles
have very low range.

00:48:54.100 --> 00:48:57.160
They deposit their kinetic
energy as heat in the material,

00:48:57.160 --> 00:48:59.500
and cause them to
glow on their own.

00:48:59.500 --> 00:49:02.410
If you produce enough heat,
if something's glowing red,

00:49:02.410 --> 00:49:06.340
you can use thermal electric
generators to capture that heat

00:49:06.340 --> 00:49:09.140
and turn it directly
into electricity.

00:49:09.140 --> 00:49:12.130
This is how things like
Voyager and, let's see,

00:49:12.130 --> 00:49:15.760
all the other space probes with
interesting names are powered.

00:49:15.760 --> 00:49:18.640
Once you're too far from the
sun for solar power to work,

00:49:18.640 --> 00:49:21.070
you need something
that doesn't turn off.

00:49:21.070 --> 00:49:23.890
So you can use RTGs,
which have long

00:49:23.890 --> 00:49:27.160
enough half-lives to produce
significant amounts of power

00:49:27.160 --> 00:49:30.010
for a long time, but
short enough half-lives so

00:49:30.010 --> 00:49:31.870
that their activity
is pretty high.

00:49:31.870 --> 00:49:34.450
And they release a lot
of energy as radiation.

00:49:34.450 --> 00:49:36.940
And that radiation is
heavy charged particles

00:49:36.940 --> 00:49:39.680
which you can capture as heat.

00:49:39.680 --> 00:49:42.370
So yeah, an actual little sphere
of plutonium that produces

00:49:42.370 --> 00:49:44.260
100 watts just sitting there.

00:49:44.260 --> 00:49:46.770
There is no way to turn it off.

00:49:46.770 --> 00:49:48.500
That's the end of the sentence.

00:49:48.500 --> 00:49:50.640
It's plutonium.

00:49:50.640 --> 00:49:53.160
